text: @AQA Me again @AQA I'm trying to download the results from ERA reports but absolutely nothing seems to be happening. Is it just being slow? Will I be able to see my students' results before they arrive to school at 9am?

@AQA I hope so. I appreciate you have a new system but, quite frankly, this new system just isn't good enough if we can't use it to access what we need to access. I sincerely hope tomorrow isn't a repeat of last week's fiasco.

@AQA Will it actually be available from 8am or will whatever happened on A Level results day happen again? Also, is there a reason why the time has changed from 6am, as was the case when we used eAQA?

@AQA It worked after 1pm.

Can we expect the same for GCSE results next week or will we be able to see our students' results from 6am, like we have done in previous years via eAQA?
@AQA Any idea when this will be resolved? I'd like to be able to look at the breakdown of marks and would like to do that today so it doesn't eat up another day of my hols!
@AQA It's 8:58 now and I can't see the results. I have the access so that's not an issue.
@AQA @AQAEnglish Any idea at all? Students will be here in 5 minutes and I'd like to be able to support/celebrate/guide them, with knowledge of their grades!
